			<ns0:name>cstefan...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/113511172007743761909/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
The renderer thread, and thus the UI, blocks during sel_ldr operations such as validation.  

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
This makes Chrome's UI seem sluggish or even blocked during validation of large nexes.

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
Make the interaction asynchronous so that the renderer thread is not blocked on long-running sel_ldr operations.

&lt;b&gt;- Exit criteria:&lt;/b&gt;
User can interact with page content even while sel_ldr is busy validating.

&lt;b&gt;- Anticipated impact:&lt;/b&gt;
Happier users and NaCl developers</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-08-03T22:30:53.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-07-25T22:48:26.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Duplicate</ns2:status><ns2:state>closed</ns2:state><ns0:title>Make sel_ldr and plugin interaction asynchronous, in particular during validation, for more responsive UI</ns0:title><ns2:label>Type-Enhancement</ns2:label><ns2:label>Pri-1</ns2:label><ns2:label>Component-Pepper</ns2:label><ns2:label>OS-All</ns2:label><ns2:label>Mstone-15</ns2:label><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/2088/comments/full" rel="replies" type="application/atom+xml" /><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=2088" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/full/2088" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><ns2:stars>1</ns2:stars><ns2:closedDate>2011-08-03T22:30:53.000Z</ns2:closedDate><ns2:id>2088</ns2:id><ns2:mergedInto>
